turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You're the only one I know who loves his parents.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I know.  It went out of style, didn't it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's okay.  It's a good thing.  You know, it's lovely here and the air is sweet.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: So you're not sorry you came?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, not sorry, but I'm not going to stay.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Why?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: In the first place, your mother as much as told me to go.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You saw that and then you've been kind of--

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, kind of embarrassed ever since I got here.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: The trouble is I planned on sneaking up on you over a period of a week or so.  But they take it for granted that we're all set.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I knew they would, your mother, anyway.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: How did you know?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: From her point of view, why else would I come?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well wouldn't you want to?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I guess you know this is why I asked you to come.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I guess this is why I came.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Ann, I love you.  I love you a great deal.  I love you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I have no imagination.  That's all I know to tell you.  I'm embarrassing you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I didn't want to tell it to you here.  I wanted someplace we'd never been; someplace where we'd be brand new to each other.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You think this is wrong, don't you; this yard, this chair?  I want you to be ready for me.  I don't want to win you away from anything.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Chris, I've been ready a long, long time.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Then he's gone forever?  You're sure?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I almost got married two years ago.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Why didn't you?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You started to write me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You felt something that far back?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Every day since.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Anne, why didn't you let me know?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I was waiting for you, Chris.  'Til then, you never wrote and when you did, what did you say?  You sure can be ambiguous, you know.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Anne, give me a kiss.  Give me a -

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I kissed you.  I kissed Annie.  How long, how long I've waited to kiss you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I'll never forgive you.  Why did you wait all these years?  All I've done is sit around and wonder if I was crazy for thinking of you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Anne, we're going to live now.  I'm going to make you so happy.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not like that you're not.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I kissed you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Like Larry's brother.  Do it like you, Chris.  What is it, Chris?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Let's drive somewhere.  I want to be alone with you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, what is it, Chris?  Your mother?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No, no, nothing like that.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Then what's wrong.  Even in your letters, there was something ashamed.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yes, I suppose there has been.  But it's going from me.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You've got to tell me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I don't know where to start.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It wouldn't work this way.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It's all mixed up with so many other things.  You remember overseas, I was in command of a company?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yeah, sure.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well I lost them.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: How many?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Just about all.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, gees.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It takes a little time to toss that off because they weren't just men.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: For instance, one time it'd been raining several days.  And this kid came to me and gave me his last pair of dry socks; put them in my pocket.  That's only a little thing, but that's the kind of guys I had.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: They didn't die.  They killed themselves for each other.  I mean that exactly.  A little more selfish and they'd have been here today.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: And I got this idea watching them go down, everything was being destroyed, see?  But, to me, it seemed there was one new thing that was made,

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: a kind of responsibility.  Man for man.  You understand me?  And then I went home and it was incredible.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: There was no meaning in it here.  The whole thing to them was some sort of bus accident.  Then I went to work for dad and that whole rat race again.  I felt, what you said, ashamed somehow

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: because nobody was changed.  It seemed to make suckers out of a lot of guys.  I felt wrong to be alive;

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: to open that bank book; to drive the new car; to see the new refrigerator.  I mean, you can take these things out of a war, but when you drive the new car, you have to know that it came out of the love a man can have for a man.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You have to be a little better because of that.  Otherwise, we have is really loot and there's blood on it.  I don't want to take any of it.  I guess that included you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: And do you still feel that way?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I want you now, Annie.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Because you mustn't feel that way anymore, Chris.  Because you have a right to everything you have, everything, Chris; to me, too.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: And your money, there's nothing wrong in your money.  Your father put hundreds of planes in the air.  You should be proud.  A man should be paid for that.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Annie, Annie, I'm going to make you a fortune.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What'll I do with a fortune?
